        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 3:19PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Morrilton, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Morrilton...                      Oppelo...
Perry...                          Bethlehem...
Petit Jean State Park...          Sequoya Park...
Lanty...                          Hill Creek...
Solgohachia...                    Cleveland...
St. Vincent...                    Blick...
Hattieville...                    Middleton...
Springfield...                    Birdtown...
Ada...                            Blackwell...
Overcup...                        Wonderview...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
